The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                The BCom Part II general (1+1+1 system) and BCom Part I general (2+1) exams of Calcutta University have been deferred from June 10 to June 15. The non-major papers of BCom Part I and II major (1+1+1), too, will be held on June 15. The BCom Part I general (1+1+1) exams and non-major papers of BCom Part I major (1+1+1) have been changed from June 17 to June 22.    The copper coils of three air-conditioners in the private wards of SSKM Hospitals Woodburn Block were missing on Monday. An FIR has been lodged.    Dipali Ghosh, 68, the sister-in-law of Joykrishna Ghosh, the confidential assistant to Jyoti Basu, was found dead at her BD Block home in Salt Lake on Monday morning. Police said she had been suffering from depression because of her failing health. The retired schoolteacher lived with her son and daughter-in-law.    A 28-year-old woman was found hanging in her in-laws house in Tollygunge on Monday afternoon. Rubi Dass father has alleged that his daughter was tortured for dowry.                                                                                                                                                                   
